==Galician==
===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|gl|xenxebre}}
===Etymology===
Attested since circa 1409 ({{m|gl||gengivre}}). From {{der|gl|ML.|gingiber}}, {{m|la|zingeber}}, from {{der|gl|la|zingiberī}}, from {{der|gl|grc|ζιγγίβερις}}, from {{der|gl|psu|सिङ्गबेर|tr=siṅgabera}}, from {{der|gl|sa|शृङ्गवेर}}) (influenced by {{m|sa|शृङ्गं|t=horn}}), from {{der|gl|oty|tr=iṅci|5=ginger}} + {{m|oty|tr=vēr|4=root}} (modern {{cog|ta|இஞ்சி|t=ginger}} + {{m|ta|வேர்|t=root}}).
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|gl|[ʃenˈʃiβɾɪ]}}
===Noun===
{{gl-noun|m}}
# [[ginger]] (plant and spice)
#* '''1409''', G. Pérez Barcala (ed.), ''A tradución galega do "Liber de medicina equorum" de Joradanus Ruffus''. Santiago de Compostela: USC, page 175:
#*: ''filla tres dramas de cravos girofes e tres onças de galingal e outro tanto de cardomomo e outro tanto de '''gengivre''' e outro tanto d’alcoravina e outro tanto de canela, e a semente do fuuncho en maior contia destas todas.''
